# Bridges

- The bridge pattern is used to connect two modules / capabilities.
- The bridge MUST have an interface, declared in the application layer `src/CSharpModulith.Capability.<Name>/Application/Bridges/<OtherCapabilityName>BridgeInterface.cs` (use the `Interface` suffix; do **not** use the `I` prefix).
- The bridge implementation MUST be in the infrastructure layer `src/CSharpModulith.Capability.<Name>/Infrastructure/Bridges/<OtherCapabilityName>Bridge.cs` and implement that interface.
- A bridge implementation MUST use the facade from another module, because direct module to module communication is allowed ONLY through the bridge
